              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " function is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server designed to calculate the fiscal year based on a given date. Scalar functions return a single value and are used to encapsulate reusable logic that can be applied to individual rows in a query."
